<section id="s1" class="chapter">
  <h2 class="section-title">1. Executive Summary &amp; Maturity Score</h2>

  <p>Nex is an ambitious, philosophically grounded, agent-native graph computation runtime. The core premise — seven Hermetically and Yoruba-coded primitives forming a self-modifying, multi-agent interpreter — is genuinely innovative. The project ships 24 TypeScript modules, 28 Markdown documents, and a complete build/gateway stack, all with <strong>zero external runtime dependencies</strong>.</p>

  <p>However, the gap between documentation ambition and code reality is significant. Several critical features described in the documentation (actual LLM integration, distributed consensus, real filesystem deployment) exist only as stubs or simulation. The security posture has serious vulnerabilities in the production gateway, and the absence of cycle-detection in the interpreter creates a denial-of-service vector. The project is <strong>prototype-grade</strong> with strong architectural vision — elevated to production requires targeted, systematic work.</p>

